        {
          "block_id": "p2_b0",
          "block_type": "heading",
          "text": "Multicollinearity",
          "bbox": [
            0.023438,
            0.040347,
            0.256965,
            0.053193
          ],
          "reading_order": 0
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p2_b1",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I Multicollinearity: When explanatory variables have some",
          "bbox": [
            0.099839,
            0.23268,
            0.745452,
            0.05877
          ],
          "reading_order": 1
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p2_b2",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "strong linear relationship, we say that there exists\nmulticollinearity. In other words, the multicollinearity occurs\nwhen one of explanatory variables can almost be explained by\nother explanatory variables.",
          "bbox": [
            0.138258,
            0.301809,
            0.77445,
            0.204755
          ],
          "reading_order": 2
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p2_b3",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I Intuitively, if there is multicollinearity, at least one explanatory",
          "bbox": [
            0.099839,
            0.517511,
            0.821129,
            0.05877
          ],
          "reading_order": 3
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p2_b4",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "variable is redundant and it would make our analysis\ncomplicated without providing any useful information.",
          "bbox": [
            0.138258,
            0.58664,
            0.677561,
            0.095218
          ],
          "reading_order": 4
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p2_b5",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I Theoretically, multicollinearity could cause instable regression",
          "bbox": [
            0.099839,
            0.692801,
            0.80768,
            0.05877
          ],
          "reading_order": 5
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p2_b6",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "estimator and lack of accuracy.",
          "bbox": [
            0.138258,
            0.76193,
            0.390585,
            0.040449
          ],
          "reading_order": 6
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p2_b7",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Chapter 9 Analysis of collinear data",
          "bbox": [
            0.523436,
            0.971541,
            0.269213,
            0.022625
          ],
          "reading_order": 7
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_number": 3,
      "width": 362.8349914550781,
      "height": 272.1260070800781,
      "ocr_used": false,
      "blocks": [
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b0",
          "block_type": "heading",
          "text": "Detection of multicollinearity",
          "bbox": [
            0.023438,
            0.040347,
            0.466566,
            0.053193
          ],
          "reading_order": 0
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b1",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "There might be multicollinearity if you observe one or more than one of\nthe followings:",
          "bbox": [
            0.078124,
            0.164344,
            0.823263,
            0.085267
          ],
          "reading_order": 1
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b2",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I Coeﬃcients of variables that are expected to be important have",
          "bbox": [
            0.101867,
            0.269454,
            0.76844,
            0.053671
          ],
          "reading_order": 2
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b3",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "large standard errors.",
          "bbox": [
            0.138258,
            0.331289,
            0.242061,
            0.03694
          ],
          "reading_order": 3
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b4",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I The algebraic signs of the estimated coeﬃcients do not conform to",
          "bbox": [
            0.101867,
            0.388072,
            0.806818,
            0.053671
          ],
          "reading_order": 4
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b5",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "prior expectations.",
          "bbox": [
            0.138258,
            0.449907,
            0.210729,
            0.03694
          ],
          "reading_order": 5
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b6",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I Large changes in the estimated coeﬃcients when a variable is added",
          "bbox": [
            0.101867,
            0.50669,
            0.819921,
            0.053671
          ],
          "reading_order": 6
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b7",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "or deleted.",
          "bbox": [
            0.138258,
            0.568525,
            0.120567,
            0.03694
          ],
          "reading_order": 7
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b8",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I Large changes in the coeﬃcients when a data point is altered or",
          "bbox": [
            0.101867,
            0.625308,
            0.773242,
            0.053671
          ],
          "reading_order": 8
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b9",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "dropped.",
          "bbox": [
            0.138258,
            0.687143,
            0.100437,
            0.03694
          ],
          "reading_order": 9
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b10",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I There exists at least one pair of explanatory variables with high",
          "bbox": [
            0.101867,
            0.743926,
            0.764931,
            0.053671
          ],
          "reading_order": 10
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p3_b11",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "correlation.\n(Caution:\n)",
          "bbox": [
            0.138258,
            0.805764,
            0.754223,
            0.085263
          ],
          "reading_order": 11
        },
        {
