        {
          "block_id": "p4_b0",
          "block_type": "heading",
          "text": "Variance Inﬂation Factor (VIF)",
          "bbox": [
            0.023438,
            0.040347,
            0.497893,
            0.053193
          ],
          "reading_order": 0
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b1",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I In a multiple linear regression, Y = β0 + β1x1 + . . . + βpxp, the",
          "bbox": [
            0.101867,
            0.181253,
            0.775258,
            0.055938
          ],
          "reading_order": 1
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b2",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "variance inﬂation factor is deﬁned as",
          "bbox": [
            0.138258,
            0.243087,
            0.420174,
            0.03694
          ],
          "reading_order": 2
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b3",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "VIF(xj) =\n1\n1 −R2",
          "bbox": [
            0.419607,
            0.307281,
            0.216242,
            0.112485
          ],
          "reading_order": 3
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b4",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "j",
          "bbox": [
            0.6247,
            0.375604,
            0.009072,
            0.025627
          ],
          "reading_order": 4
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b5",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "ㄴ",
          "bbox": [
            0.916248,
            0.376978,
            0.003947,
            0.004157
          ],
          "reading_order": 5
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b6",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "where R2",
          "bbox": [
            0.138258,
            0.437373,
            0.107669,
            0.041657
          ],
          "reading_order": 6
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b7",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "1 is the multiple correlation coeﬃcient when you regress X1\non (X2, . . . , Xn) and similarly R2",
          "bbox": [
            0.138258,
            0.442091,
            0.782235,
            0.088011
          ],
          "reading_order": 7
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b8",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "j is the multiple correlation\ncoeﬃcient when you regress Xj on (X1, . . . , Xj−1, Xj+1, Xn)",
          "bbox": [
            0.138258,
            0.490418,
            0.714624,
            0.105976
          ],
          "reading_order": 8
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b9",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I Rule of thumb: VIF(xj)>10 ! a signal for multicollinearity",
          "bbox": [
            0.101867,
            0.595527,
            0.723731,
            0.076441
          ],
          "reading_order": 9
        },
        {
          "block_id": "p4_b10",
          "block_type": "paragraph",
